Q_DESC:
Write an efficient C function to return maximum occurring character in the input string e.g., if input string is test then function should return t.

INPUT
First line contains the string
OUTPUT
The output prints maximum occurred character
TESTCASE_1:
sample string
###---###SEPERATOR---###---
Max occurring character is s
TESTCASE_2:
test
###---###SEPERATOR---###---
Max occurring character is t
TESTCASE_3:
aaabbbbc
###---###SEPERATOR---###---
Max occurring character is b
